<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274D1206A9033F49FC65F7CB" bold="true" box="[848,981,2065,2089]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Distribution</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="34FF764B274D1206A9A93F49FBDAF7CA" box="[1018,1130,2065,2088]" name="Singapore" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Singapore</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04F26550274C1207AA2D3795FE97FDA7" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274C1207AA2D3795FE97FDA7" blockId="5.[126,766,205,581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274C1207AA2D3795FEB1FF07" bold="true" box="[126,257,205,229]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274C1207AA2D3795FF52FF07" bold="true" box="[126,226,205,229]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Remarks</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D58274C1207A8B13796FF50FEE7" authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plumatus" status="new species">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274C1207A8B13796FF50FEE7" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">H. plumatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="65AF57B2274C1207AABE37B6FEC0FEE7" box="[237,368,238,261]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but may be separated from the latter by the cercus being strongly curved and nearly geniculate. 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D58274C1207AA2D3676FE24FEA7" authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[126,404,302,325]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" status="new species">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274C1207AA2D3676FE24FEA7" box="[126,404,302,325]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Hercostomus brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="65AF57B2274C1207ABF63676FD9DFEA7" box="[421,557,302,325]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is also somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D58274C1207AABE3616FD3AFE87" authority="Becker, 1922" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1922" box="[237,650,334,357]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congruens">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274C1207AABE3616FE40FE87" box="[237,496,334,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Hercostomus congruens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="28794B2A274C1207ABAB3616FD3AFE87" author="Becker, T" box="[504,650,334,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 247" refId="ref7585" refString="Becker, T. H., 1922. Dipterologische Studien Dolichopodidae der Indo-Australischen Region. Capita Zoologica, 1: 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1922">Becker, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry id="34FF764B274C1207AAEB3636FEB8FE67" box="[184,264,366,389]" name="Taiwan" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
in having the first flagellomere as long as wide and all coxae yellow, but may be separated by the epandrial lobe being wide apically, aedeagus with 2 inner denticles and cercus strongly curved, nearly geniculate. In 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D58274C1207A8363696FD46FE07" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1922" box="[613,758,462,485]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congruens">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274C1207A8363696FD46FE07" box="[613,758,462,485]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">H. congruens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the lateral epandrial lobe is rather narrow apically, aedeagus is without denticles and cercus has a rounded ventral apex (
<bibRefCitation id="28794B2A274C1207AAD63576FEACFDA7" author="Becker, T" box="[133,284,558,581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 247" refId="ref7585" refString="Becker, T. H., 1922. Dipterologische Studien Dolichopodidae der Indo-Australischen Region. Capita Zoologica, 1: 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1922">Becker, 1922</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
